{"id":"1590","name":"Full Power","tagline":"Turn off Airplane Mode and Low Power Mode and Turn on WiFi, Bluetooth, and Cellular Data","icon":"ios13 c4274264319 g59764","latest":"11262","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>This shortcut turns off airplane mode and low power mode and turns on WiFi, Bluetooth, and cellular data. It is very useful when you are done rapid-charging your phone or getting off a flight.</p>\n<p>It can even be run from your Apple Watch to make these settings on your phone! It doesn't effect the Watch settings at all. </p>\n<p>This shortcut can be run stand-alone or from another shortcut such as <em>RoutineKit</em> or <em>My RoutineKit</em> which will pull information from various other shortcuts like this together.</p>\n<p>This shortcut incorporates the <em>UpdateKit</em> shortcut so users can receive a notification to download a new version when updates are available.</p>\n<p><em>Keywords: low power, charging, WiFi, Bluetooth, cellular, airplane, mode, RoutineKit.</em></p>\n<p><em>Supports: RoutineKit, UpdateKit.</em></p>\n<p><em>Compatibility: iPhone, iPad, Apple Watch and HomePod (changes iPhone settings).</em></p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.2 - Oct. 6, 2019, 7:08 p.m.</strong></p><p>Fix for UpdateKit with iOS 13. Also added an option to display the results in a notification instead of an alert when called from RoutineKit.</p>"}